# ─── Exclusions for the Docker build context ────────────────────────────────
# The Dockerfile uses `COPY . .` to grab the whole repo; this file shapes
# what actually lands in the image. Goal: ship the FastAPI + ML modules and
# pre-trained models, drop everything else.

# Python dev artifacts
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# Caches + tooling
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.benchmarks/

# Secrets — never bake these into the image.
.env
.env.local
.env.*
.streamlit/secrets.toml
DB password.rtf
*.rtf

# Streamlit UI files — not part of the API runtime. Excluding them keeps
# the image small and prevents Streamlit's dependencies from being pulled
# in by transitive imports.
app.py
analyzer.py
batch_scanner.py
benchmark.py
diag_importance.py
backtester.py
auto_retrain.py
daily_briefing.py
sentiment_analyzer.py
paper_trader.py
predictions_page.py
track_record_page.py
dashboard_page.py
portfolio_page.py
watchlist_page.py
watchlist.py
stock_detail_page.py
recover_from_v1_log.py
backfill_regimes.py
backfill_top_features.py
migrate_to_sqlite.py

# Local prediction store + scratch databases. The deployed backend uses
# Supabase (USE_SUPABASE=true in render.yaml), so these aren't needed.
.predictions/

# Local-only / dev artifacts
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.xlsx.bak
~$*.xlsx
retrain.log
*.log

# Git internals
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# Documentation — useful for humans, dead weight for runtime
docs/
*.md
PHASE_*
SUPABASE_SETUP.md
DEPLOY.md

# Tests + scripts — not used at runtime
tests/
scripts/

# Other deploy configs (not needed inside the image)
fly.toml
render.yaml

# Notes:
#   • .models/ is INCLUDED (no exclude rule for it) — the joblib files are
#     required for inference. Each is ~1-5MB, ~250 tickers → image will
#     be ~1GB. Slower builds but acceptable for free-tier hobby use.
#   • supabase/migrations/ is INCLUDED for reference, even though Supabase
#     applies them out-of-band. Tiny SQL files, harmless to ship.
